N.B.  Because repertoire faceting depends on in-database indexing modules, tests must be run against
an actual Postgres instance (not sqlite).  To create the appropriate database,

1. install the PostgreSQL extensions as described in the main README
2. create and configure testing database:
     createdb -Upostgres repertoire_testing
     createlang -Upostgres plpgsql repertoire_testing
     rake faceting:postgres:load
        [ provide "repertoire_testing" at the database name prompt ]
3. upload testing data
     psql -Upostgres repertoire_testing -f test/fixtures/nobelists.sql
     psql -Upostgres repertoire_testing -f test/fixtures/citizens.sql
4. run the core specs
     rake test
